This is a programming excercise in implementing Bulls and Cows.
More details of the game can be seen at
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulls_and_Cows

In the forward problem,
Computer guesses a unique 4 digit number and user is given 8 chances to guess it correctly.
For each user guess and the number of bulls and cows are displayed.

In the Reverse problem.
User Guesses a unique 4 digit number and computer guesses it within 8 Chances.
For each computer try, user inputs the number of bulls and cows.
